ve with Gucci and Balenciaga et al.=E2=80=94a tall order and false proposit=
ion. Calvin Klein is not, and never was, a luxury brand. Like Donna Karan, =
Michael Kors, Ralph Lauren, and other companies born in the post-couture er=
a, Calvin Klein derived its profits from low-margin volume items rather tha=
n expensive handbags. In the end, the dream team was stymied because the ma=
